# Optional: change port
# PORT=5000

# ---------- Developer panel (optional, maintainer only) ----------
# Long random string (8+ chars). Unlocks a small “Dev” control (bottom-right of dashboard) after you POST the same
# value to /api/dev/unlock — see DASHBOARD_QUICK_REFERENCE.md. Omit to hide the panel from everyone.
# DEV_PANEL_TOKEN=

# ---------- Google Sheet (optional) ----------
# Publish your sheet to web (File → Share → Publish to web → CSV), then paste the URL here.
# When set, the dashboard fetches live data from the sheet on each load. Multiple people can edit the sheet.
# GOOGLE_SHEET_URL=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/YOUR_SHEET_ID/export?format=csv&gid=0

# ---------- Google Ads API (optional) ----------
# Fill these to pull live Google Ads data into the dashboard.
# Get them from: Google Cloud Console, Google Ads API Center, and OAuth flow.
#
# GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN=  from Google Ads → Tools → API Center
# GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID=        from Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client
# GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET=    same OAuth client
# GOOGLE_ADS_REFRESH_TOKEN=    from one-time OAuth flow (user signs in, you exchange code for refresh_token)
# GOOGLE_ADS_CUSTOMER_ID=      the Google Ads account to query (e.g. 123-456-7890 or 1234567890)
# GOOGLE_ADS_LOGIN_CUSTOMER_ID= only if using an MCC (manager) account; the MCC ID

# ---------- TikTok Marketing API (optional) ----------
# Fill these to pull live TikTok Ads data into the dashboard.
# Get them from: TikTok for Business / TikTok Marketing API.
#
# TIKTOK_ACCESS_TOKEN=   long-lived access token for the TikTok Ads account
# TIKTOK_ADVERTISER_ID=  your TikTok Ads advertiser (account) ID
